# Overleaf MCP ŌĆö Detailed Reference (v1.8)

> **Day-to-day use:** see `CLAUDE_REFERENCE.md` (cheat sheet).  
> Load this file only when you need to understand a specific tool, class, or behaviour in depth.

---

## Architecture

```
overleaf-mcp-server.js   ŌåÉ MCP tool layer (tool definitions + request handler)
OverleafGitClient        ŌåÉ class inside same file: all git + file logic
projects.json            ŌåÉ project config: { projects: { default: { projectId, gitToken, name } } }
```

The server clones/pulls the Overleaf repo via `https://git:<token>@git.overleaf.com/<projectId>` into a temp dir (`/tmp/overleaf-<projectId>`), operates on the local files, then commits and pushes.

---

## OverleafGitClient ŌĆö method reference

### Low-level I/O
| Method | Description |
|---|---|
| `cloneOrPull()` | Ensures local repo is up-to-date |
| `readRaw(filePath)` | Read raw file content (pulls first) |
| `writeRaw(filePath, content, commitMessage)` | Write + commit + push |

### Preamble
| Method | Notes |
|---|---|
| `getPreamble(filePath)` | Returns everything before `\begin{document}` |
| `writePreamble(filePath, newPreamble, msg)` | Replaces preamble, preserves body exactly. Throws if no `\begin{document}`. |

### Headings / Sections
| Method | Notes |
|---|---|
| `_parseHeadings(content)` | Returns `[{title, type, level, index}]` for all 4 levels |
| `_headingBounds(content, title, type?)` | Returns `[start, end]` char indices of a heading block |
| `getSections(filePath, typeFilter?)` | Public; returns heading list |
| `getSectionContent(filePath, title, type?)` | Returns raw text of block |
| `writeSection(filePath, title, newContent, type?, msg)` | In-place block replace |
| `moveSection(filePath, src, anchor, position, type?, msg)` | Atomic cut-and-splice |
| `insertSection(filePath, anchor, newContent, position, anchorType?, msg)` | Insert before/after |

**Heading levels:**
```
section=1  subsection=2  subsubsection=3  paragraph=4
```
Block boundary = next heading at same or higher level (lower number).

### BibTeX
| Method | Notes |
|---|---|
| `_parseBibEntries(content)` | Returns `[{key, type, fields, rawText, start, end}]` |
| `searchBibEntries(filePath, query, field?)` | Case-insensitive partial match; searches all fields or one |
| `getBibEntry(filePath, key)` | Exact key lookup (case-insensitive) |
| `writeBibEntry(filePath, key, newEntryText, msg)` | Replaces only that entry's char range |

**BibTeX parser notes:**
- Handles `field = {value}`, `field = "value"`, `field = number`
- Nested braces in values are handled by the brace-depth walker
- `rawText` is the full original entry text including `@type{key, ...}`
- `start`/`end` are character offsets in the file ŌĆö used for precise in-place replacement

### Paragraph search
| Method | Notes |
|---|---|
| `_parseParagraphs(slice, baseOffset)` | Splits on blank lines, skips heading lines |
| `_buildLocationIndex(content)` | Returns a function `(pos, type) ŌåÆ heading title` |
| `searchParagraphs(filePath, keywords, matchAll, sectionTitle?, type?)` | Returns `[{matchedKeywords, location, text}]` |

`location` object has keys for each heading level that encloses the paragraph, e.g.:
```json
{ "section": "Introduction", "subsection": "Background" }
```

### File management
| Method | Notes |
|---|---|
| `listFiles(extension?)` | Defaults to `.tex`; pass `.bib` etc. |
| `createFile(filePath, content, msg)` | `mkdir -p` then write |
| `deleteFile(filePath, msg)` | `git rm` + push |

---

## Tool ŌåÆ method mapping

| MCP Tool | OverleafGitClient method |
|---|---|
| `list_files` | `listFiles` |
| `read_file` | `readFile` (alias for `readRaw`) |
| `create_file` | `createFile` |
| `delete_file` | `deleteFile` |
| `get_preamble` | `getPreamble` |
| `write_preamble` | `writePreamble` |
| `get_sections` | `getSections` |
| `get_section_content` | `getSectionContent` |
| `write_section` | `writeSection` |
| `move_section` | `moveSection` |
| `insert_section` | `insertSection` |
| `search_bib_entries` | `searchBibEntries` |
| `get_bib_entry` | `getBibEntry` |
| `write_bib_entry` | `writeBibEntry` |
| `search_paragraphs` | `searchParagraphs` |
| `status_summary` | `listFiles` + `getSections` |

---

## Edge cases & gotchas

- **Starred headings** (`\section*{...}`) are parsed and matched correctly
- **`write_preamble`** throws if file has no `\begin{document}` ŌĆö not safe for included files
- **`move_section`**: source and anchor must be distinct; `sectionType` applies to both
- **BibTeX `field = {nested {braces}}`**: inner braces are fine ŌĆö parser walks depth correctly
- **`search_bib_entries` with no `field`**: searches citation key AND all field values
- **All writes pull first** ŌĆö concurrent edits from Overleaf UI will be picked up before each write

---

## Adding a new tool (developer guide)

1. Add a method to `OverleafGitClient`
2. Add an entry to the `tools` array in `ListToolsRequestSchema` handler
3. Add a `case` in the `CallToolRequestSchema` switch
4. Update version string in `new Server(...)` call
5. Update both `CLAUDE_REFERENCE.md` (cheat sheet table) and this file
